item.title: How many models can a 317 actually hold?
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

As Frell said, a 317 client can hold as many models as your computers memory will let it. The problem of adding them with id’s over 15k is that of over-writing objects. My client, at normal, has about 28k models inside of it (loading the 377 cache -.-). Yet, i can only use ID’s over 15k that will show. I have edited my client to that i can use ID’s over 15k, but they must be pre-loaded OR they just wont show up.

Sum Up - Yes, 317 clients can hold as much models as your computers memory. The problem is correctly loading them from the cache.
